# C++ Coding Style (Rewrite)

Applies to `next/nlrc_vksplat/` only. Keep rules binary and checkable.

## Files and layout

- Use **`.hpp`** for headers and **`.cpp`** for sources — never `.h` or `.c`
- **`#pragma once`** in every header
- Namespace **`nlrc::vksplat`** for library code
- Paired TUs: `foo.hpp` + `foo.cpp`; declarations in hpp, definitions in cpp (templates / header-only `constexpr` in hpp when required)
- No **`using namespace`** in headers

```cpp
// BAD — ref-style header name in rewrite
#include "buffer.h"

// GOOD
#include "buffer.hpp"
```

## const and constexpr

- **`const` by default**: immutable locals, `const&` for read-only inputs, `const` member functions when state is not modified
- **`constexpr` when compile-time**: `inline constexpr` for constants (`kFoo`), `constexpr` for pure functions evaluable at compile time
- **`nullptr`** for null pointers — never `NULL` or `0`

```cpp
// BAD
char* version();
int tile_size = 16;

// GOOD
[[nodiscard]] const char* version();
inline constexpr int kTileSize = 16;
```

## Types and APIs

- Prefer **`enum class`** over unscoped `enum` (unless C/Vulkan ABI requires raw `enum`)
- Mark single-argument constructors **`explicit`** unless implicit conversion is intentional (add a brief comment)
- Apply **`[[nodiscard]]`** to getters, handles, and status/error returns

## Tooling

Naming follows [`.clang-tidy`](next/nlrc_vksplat/.clang-tidy); formatting follows [`.clang-format`](next/nlrc_vksplat/.clang-format).
